<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8660&amp;p=90599#p90599</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8660&amp;p=90599#p90599"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Fixing my NES to PlayChoice adapter]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8660&amp;p=90599#p90599"><![CDATA[
PRG /CE is combined with A14 and A13 to form the PRG RAM select signal. In previous discussions about building such a decoder circuit to add to a discrete mapper, I learned that it's made with a 74LS139 on the NES motherboard and thus delayed a few dozen nanoseconds compared to A14 and A13. Different MMC3 revisions might have different tolerances for this delay. Do Crystalis and M.C. Kids have problems when played through this adapter? They had problems on early versions of the MMC3 mapper for PowerPak because writing to the IRQ enable ports ($E000-$FFFF) would end up also writing to PRG RAM ($6000-$7FFF).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Feb 26, 2012 6:27 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
