Ok this is not a thread asking how you make one this is a thread asking for help to get  the one I made working right.<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://forums.arcade-museum.com/showpost.php?p=1608023&amp;postcount=27">http://forums.arcade-museum.com/showpos ... stcount=27</a><!-- m --><br /><br />As you can see the Powerpak loads and it has played any ROM on it including a NES test cart that checked out ok assuming it can work that way.<br /><br />Now you are probably wondering whats the problem. <br />It won't play all regular cart games, such as SMB3 as an original cart that works in a normal NES won't play but loading it with the Powerpak it plays fine.<br /><br />So I could use some help figuring this out cause I would like to make it work with all carts.<br /><br />Using the schematic from the PlayChoice and a pinout of the 72pin connector I hooked it up straight forward except on a few lines where on PlayChoice carts they go through a buffer. These lines would be VRAM /CE, PRG ROM /CE and CHR /A13, the buffer is a 74367.<br /><br />It would also be nice to know how the M82 does its selecting.<br /><br />Let me know what you think.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3348">Mr.collection</a> — Sun Feb 26, 2012 12:02 pm</p><hr />
